---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="arr-barr — The Guide" description="From empty dock to full operation in one sitting.">

<div class="page-header">
  <h1>The Guide</h1>
  <p>From empty dock to full operation</p>
</div>

<div class="guide-container">

  <!-- Progress nav -->
  <nav class="guide-nav">
    <a href="#prerequisites" class="gn-link">1. Prerequisites</a>
    <a href="#clone" class="gn-link">2. Clone</a>
    <a href="#configure" class="gn-link">3. Configure</a>
    <a href="#vpn" class="gn-link">4. VPN</a>
    <a href="#launch" class="gn-link">5. Launch</a>
    <a href="#first-request" class="gn-link">6. First Request</a>
    <a href="#friends" class="gn-link">7. Invite Friends</a>
    <a href="#faq" class="gn-link">8. FAQ</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Step 1: Prerequisites -->
  <section id="prerequisites" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <h2>What You'll Need</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Before you set sail, make sure you've got the essentials on board.</p>

    <div class="req-grid grid-no-orphan">
      <div class="req-card">
        <span class="req-icon">&#x1F5A5;</span>
        <h3>A Server</h3>
        <p>A Synology NAS, Linux box, or any machine that can run Docker 24/7. The DS920+ is our reference hardware, but anything with 4GB+ RAM works.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="req-card">
        <span class="req-icon">&#x1F433;</span>
        <h3>Docker & Compose</h3>
        <p>Docker Engine + Docker Compose v2. Synology users get this through Container Manager. Linux users: follow the <a href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/">official install guide</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="req-card">
        <span class="req-icon">&#x1F510;</span>
        <h3>A VPN Account</h3>
        <p>A VPN provider that supports WireGuard. We use ProtonVPN (paid plan). Mullvad, AirVPN, and Windscribe also work. This is not optional.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="req-card">
        <span class="req-icon">&#x1F4E6;</span>
        <h3>A Usenet Provider</h3>
        <p>At least one usenet provider (Newshosting, Frugal, etc.) and one usenet indexer (NZBgeek, NZBFinder). Torrent-only setups work too, but usenet is faster and more reliable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <strong>Budget estimate:</strong> VPN ~$5/mo + Usenet ~$10/mo + Indexer ~$0-15/yr. See the <a href="/costs">full cost breakdown</a>.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 2: Clone -->
  <section id="clone" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <h2>Clone the Repo</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Get the code on your server.</p>

    <div class="code-block">
      <div class="code-header"><span>terminal</span></div>
      <pre><code><span class="c-prompt">$</span> git clone git@github.com:TrashedPandai/arr-barr.git
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> cd arr-barr</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>This gives you everything: the Docker Compose stack, the CLI tool, config templates, and documentation.</p>

    <div class="file-tree">
      <div class="ft-title">What's in the box</div>
      <div class="ft-item"><span class="ft-file">compose.yaml</span> <span class="ft-desc">All 15 services defined</span></div>
      <div class="ft-item"><span class="ft-file">.env.example</span> <span class="ft-desc">Template for your secrets</span></div>
      <div class="ft-item"><span class="ft-dir">.cli/</span> <span class="ft-desc">The <code>arr</code> command toolkit</span></div>
      <div class="ft-item"><span class="ft-dir">templates/</span> <span class="ft-desc">Config templates for Bazarr, Transmission, LazyLibrarian</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 3: Configure -->
  <section id="configure" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <h2>Configure Your Environment</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Copy the example env and fill in your details.</p>

    <div class="code-block">
      <div class="code-header"><span>terminal</span></div>
      <pre><code><span class="c-prompt">$</span> cp .env.example .env
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> nano .env</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="env-table">
      <div class="env-row env-header"><span>Variable</span><span>What it does</span></div>
      <div class="env-row"><span><code>DATA_ROOT</code></span><span>Where all media and downloads live. Single mount = hardlinks work.</span></div>
      <div class="env-row"><span><code>PUID</code> / <code>PGID</code></span><span>User/group ID for file ownership. Synology: <code>1026:100</code>.</span></div>
      <div class="env-row"><span><code>TZ</code></span><span>Your timezone. e.g. <code>America/New_York</code>.</span></div>
      <div class="env-row"><span><code>VPN_*</code></span><span>WireGuard credentials from your VPN provider (see next step).</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <strong>Never commit your <code>.env</code></strong> &mdash; it contains VPN private keys and API secrets. It's already in <code>.gitignore</code>.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 4: VPN -->
  <section id="vpn" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <h2>Set Up Your VPN</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">All traffic routes through an encrypted WireGuard tunnel for privacy.</p>

    <div class="vpn-flow">
      <div class="vpn-step">
        <div class="vpn-num">A</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Get your WireGuard config</strong>
          <p>Log into your VPN provider's website. Generate a WireGuard configuration file. You need the private key, endpoint address, and server public key.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="vpn-step">
        <div class="vpn-num">B</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Fill in the <code>.env</code> VPN section</strong>
          <p>Copy the private key, endpoint, and public key into the corresponding <code>WIREGUARD_*</code> variables.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="vpn-step">
        <div class="vpn-num">C</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Pick a server</strong>
          <p>Choose a server that supports port forwarding (ProtonVPN: any P2P server). Netherlands and Switzerland are solid choices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <strong>Kill switch is on by default.</strong> If the VPN drops, all outbound traffic is blocked until the tunnel reconnects.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 5: Launch -->
  <section id="launch" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <h2>Launch the Stack</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">One command to rule them all.</p>

    <div class="code-block">
      <div class="code-header"><span>terminal</span></div>
      <pre><code><span class="c-comment"># Run the setup wizard (creates directories, copies templates)</span>
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> arr setup

<span class="c-comment"># Start all 15 services</span>
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> arr start

<span class="c-comment"># Check that everything is alive</span>
<span class="c-prompt">$</span> arr health</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>First boot takes a few minutes while containers pull their images. After that, you should see all 15 crew members reporting healthy.</p>

    <div class="code-block">
      <div class="code-header"><span>output</span></div>
      <pre><code><span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> gluetun ............  <span class="c-green">tunnel up</span>        23ms
<span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> transmission ........  <span class="c-green">healthy</span>          41ms
<span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> sabnzbd .............  <span class="c-green">healthy</span>          38ms
<span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> radarr ..............  <span class="c-green">healthy</span>          52ms
<span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> sonarr ..............  <span class="c-green">healthy</span>          47ms
<span class="c-green">&#x25CF;</span> jellyfin ............  <span class="c-green">healthy</span>          31ms

<span class="c-green">15/15 crew members reporting</span>         all systems nominal</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 6: First Request -->
  <section id="first-request" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">6</div>
    <h2>Your First Request</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Let's add something to your library and see the pipeline in action.</p>

    <div class="request-flow">
      <div class="rf-step">
        <div class="rf-badge rf-purple">1</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Open Jellyseerr</strong>
          <p>Navigate to <code>http://your-server:5055</code>. Search for a movie or show.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rf-arrow">&#x2193;</div>
      <div class="rf-step">
        <div class="rf-badge rf-cyan">2</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Hit Request</strong>
          <p>Jellyseerr sends the request to Radarr (movies) or Sonarr (TV). They search 12 indexers in parallel via Prowlarr.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rf-arrow">&#x2193;</div>
      <div class="rf-step">
        <div class="rf-badge rf-green">3</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Best release auto-selected</strong>
          <p>48 custom formats score each result. The highest-scoring release is grabbed through the encrypted VPN tunnel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rf-arrow">&#x2193;</div>
      <div class="rf-step">
        <div class="rf-badge rf-pink">4</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Hardlinked &amp; ready</strong>
          <p>File is renamed, hardlinked to your library (zero extra disk space), artwork fetched, subtitles queued. Jellyfin sees it immediately.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <strong>Typical time:</strong> 2&ndash;10 minutes from request to watching, depending on file size and connection speed.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 7: Invite Friends -->
  <section id="friends" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">7</div>
    <h2>Invite Friends</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Your library is better with friends. Here's how to get your crew onboard.</p>

    <div class="friends-grid">
      <div class="friend-card">
        <h3>For Watchers</h3>
        <p>Create Jellyfin accounts for friends. They stream your shared library through any Jellyfin client &mdash; phone, TV, browser, Roku, anything.</p>
        <span class="friend-tag">Zero setup for them</span>
      </div>
      <div class="friend-card">
        <h3>For Requesters</h3>
        <p>Give them Jellyseerr access. They browse, request, and track &mdash; it shows up in the library automatically. No technical knowledge needed.</p>
        <span class="friend-tag">They just search and click</span>
      </div>
      <div class="friend-card">
        <h3>For Operators</h3>
        <p>Friends who want to run their own stack: fork the repo, follow this guide, and they're live. The CLI handles everything.</p>
        <span class="friend-tag">Full stack in 30 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 8: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="guide-step gs">
    <div class="step-num">8</div>
    <h2>Troubleshooting &amp; FAQ</h2>
    <p class="step-desc">Common questions from new crew members.</p>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>My download is stuck / not starting</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Run <code>arr vpn</code> to check VPN status. If the tunnel is down, downloads are blocked by the kill switch (this is intentional). Check your WireGuard credentials in <code>.env</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Jellyfin says "No compatible streams"</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>The file needs transcoding but your server can't keep up. Enable hardware transcoding in Jellyfin settings (QSV for Intel, VAAPI for others). On a Synology DS920+, QSV handles 4K with ease.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>A service won't start</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Run <code>arr logs &lt;service&gt;</code> to see what's wrong. Common causes: port conflict, missing directory, or bad permissions. <code>arr doctor</code> can diagnose most issues automatically.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do I update everything?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p><code>arr update</code> pulls the latest code and recreates containers with new images. Your config and media are never touched &mdash; they live in persistent volumes.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is this legal?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Every tool in the arr-barr stack is 100% legal, open-source software. They are designed for managing and automating personal media libraries. Users are responsible for ensuring their use complies with applicable copyright laws in their jurisdiction. The VPN provides network privacy as a standard security practice.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I run this on a Raspberry Pi?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Technically possible on a Pi 4/5, but not recommended. The arr apps are memory-hungry and transcoding needs real CPU/GPU power. A used mini PC or NAS is a much better experience.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How much disk space do I need?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Depends on your library goals. A starter library of ~100 movies + ~30 shows in 1080p runs about 2&ndash;3 TB. Hardlinks mean downloads and library files share the same disk space &mdash; no duplication.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <div class="guide-cta gs">
    <h2>You're ready to sail</h2>
    <p>Questions? Check the <a href="/docs">docs</a> or dig into the <a href="/docs/diagrams">architecture</a>.</p>
  </div>

</div>

</Base>

<style>
  .page-header { text-align:center; padding:50px 24px 10px; }
  .page-header h1 {
    font-size:clamp(1.8rem,5vw,2.5rem); font-weight:700;
    background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--indigo),var(--purple));
    -webkit-background-clip:text; background-clip:text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;
  }
  .page-header p { color:var(--text-dim); font-size:1.05rem; margin-top:6px; }

  .guide-container { max-width:860px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 24px 60px; }

  /* Progress nav */
  .guide-nav {
    display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:6px; justify-content:center;
    padding:20px 0 40px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom:40px; position:sticky; top:56px; z-index:100;
    background:rgba(10,14,26,0.92); backdrop-filter:blur(12px);
  }
  .gn-link {
    font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:500; color:var(--text-muted);
    padding:5px 12px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);
    text-decoration:none; transition:all 0.2s;
  }
  .gn-link:hover { color:var(--indigo); border-color:rgba(99,102,241,0.3); }

  /* Steps */
  .guide-step {
    padding:40px 0; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(30,41,59,0.4);
  }
  .guide-step:last-of-type { border-bottom:none; }
  .step-num {
    display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    width:36px; height:36px; border-radius:50%;
    background:rgba(99,102,241,0.1); border:1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.25);
    color:var(--indigo); font-weight:700; font-size:0.9rem;
    margin-bottom:12px;
  }
  .guide-step h2 { font-size:1.4rem; color:#f1f5f9; margin-bottom:6px; }
  .step-desc { color:var(--text-dim); font-size:0.95rem; margin-bottom:20px; }

  /* Prerequisite cards */
  .req-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:12px; margin-bottom:16px; }
  .req-card {
    background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:12px; padding:18px;
  }
  .req-icon { font-size:1.4rem; display:block; margin-bottom:8px; }
  .req-card h3 { font-size:0.95rem; color:#e0e6f0; margin-bottom:4px; }
  .req-card p { font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.6; }

  /* Code blocks */
  .code-block {
    background:#080c16; border:1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.15);
    border-radius:10px; overflow:hidden; margin:16px 0;
  }
  .code-header {
    padding:8px 14px; background:rgba(15,22,41,0.8);
    border-bottom:1px solid rgba(30,41,59,0.6);
    font-size:0.68rem; color:var(--text-muted);
    font-family:'SF Mono','Fira Code',monospace;
  }
  .code-block pre {
    padding:14px 16px; margin:0; overflow-x:auto;
    font-family:'SF Mono','Fira Code',Consolas,monospace;
    font-size:0.82rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-dim);
  }
  .code-block code { background:none; border:none; padding:0; font-size:inherit; color:inherit; }
  .c-prompt { color:var(--yellow); }
  .c-comment { color:var(--text-muted); }
  .c-green { color:var(--green); }

  /* File tree */
  .file-tree {
    background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:10px; padding:16px; margin-top:16px;
  }
  .ft-title { font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:600; color:var(--text-muted); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.08em; margin-bottom:10px; }
  .ft-item { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:10px; padding:4px 0; font-size:0.85rem; }
  .ft-file { color:var(--cyan); font-family:'SF Mono','Fira Code',monospace; font-size:0.8rem; }
  .ft-dir { color:var(--yellow); font-family:'SF Mono','Fira Code',monospace; font-size:0.8rem; }
  .ft-desc { color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.78rem; }

  /* Env table */
  .env-table {
    border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:10px; overflow:hidden; margin:16px 0;
  }
  .env-row {
    display:grid; grid-template-columns:180px 1fr; padding:10px 16px;
    font-size:0.85rem; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(30,41,59,0.4);
  }
  .env-row:last-child { border-bottom:none; }
  .env-header { background:var(--surface); font-weight:600; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.06em; }
  .env-row span:first-child { color:var(--cyan); }
  .env-row span:last-child { color:var(--text-dim); }

  /* Tip / Warn boxes */
  .tip-box, .warn-box {
    padding:14px 18px; border-radius:10px; font-size:0.85rem;
    line-height:1.6; margin:16px 0;
  }
  .tip-box {
    background:rgba(16,185,129,0.06); border:1px solid rgba(16,185,129,0.2);
    color:var(--text-dim);
  }
  .tip-box strong { color:#6ee7b7; }
  .warn-box {
    background:rgba(245,158,11,0.06); border:1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.2);
    color:var(--text-dim);
  }
  .warn-box strong { color:#fcd34d; }

  /* VPN flow */
  .vpn-flow { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:16px; margin:16px 0; }
  .vpn-step {
    display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:flex-start;
    background:rgba(16,185,129,0.04); border:1px solid rgba(16,185,129,0.15);
    border-radius:10px; padding:16px;
  }
  .vpn-num {
    flex-shrink:0; width:30px; height:30px; border-radius:50%;
    background:rgba(16,185,129,0.15); color:#6ee7b7;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    font-weight:700; font-size:0.85rem;
  }
  .vpn-step strong { color:#a7f3d0; font-size:0.9rem; }
  .vpn-step p { color:var(--text-dim); font-size:0.82rem; margin-top:4px; line-height:1.6; }

  /* Request flow */
  .request-flow { display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:center; gap:0; margin:16px 0; }
  .rf-step {
    display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:flex-start; width:100%;
    background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:10px; padding:16px;
  }
  .rf-badge {
    flex-shrink:0; width:30px; height:30px; border-radius:50%;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    font-weight:700; font-size:0.85rem;
  }
  .rf-purple { background:rgba(192,132,252,0.15); color:var(--purple); }
  .rf-cyan { background:rgba(34,211,238,0.15); color:var(--cyan); }
  .rf-green { background:rgba(74,222,128,0.15); color:var(--green); }
  .rf-pink { background:rgba(244,114,182,0.15); color:var(--pink); }
  .rf-step strong { color:#e0e6f0; font-size:0.9rem; }
  .rf-step p { color:var(--text-dim); font-size:0.82rem; margin-top:4px; line-height:1.6; }
  .rf-arrow { color:var(--text-muted); font-size:1.2rem; padding:4px 0; }

  /* Friends grid */
  .friends-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:12px; margin-top:16px; }
  .friend-card {
    background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:12px; padding:20px;
  }
  .friend-card h3 { font-size:0.95rem; color:#e0e6f0; margin-bottom:6px; }
  .friend-card p { font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:10px; }
  .friend-tag {
    display:inline-block; font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:500;
    color:var(--indigo); background:rgba(99,102,241,0.1);
    border:1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.2); padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-list { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px; margin-top:16px; }
  .faq-item {
    background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:10px; overflow:hidden;
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    padding:14px 18px; cursor:pointer; font-size:0.9rem;
    font-weight:500; color:#e0e6f0; list-style:none;
    display:flex; align-items:center; gap:10px;
  }
  .faq-item summary::before { content:'+ '; color:var(--indigo); font-weight:700; font-family:monospace; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::before { content:'- '; }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display:none; }
  .faq-body { padding:0 18px 14px; }
  .faq-body p { font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; }

  /* Bottom CTA */
  .guide-cta {
    text-align:center; padding:40px 0 20px;
  }
  .guide-cta h2 { font-size:1.3rem; color:#f1f5f9; margin-bottom:6px; }
  .guide-cta p { color:var(--text-dim); font-size:0.95rem; }

  /* GSAP fade targets */
  .gs { opacity:0; transform:translateY(20px); }

  /* Responsive */
  @media(max-width:768px) {
